            </div>

            <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>
            <p>Should you buy this dip? <strong>It depends entirely on your situation.</strong></p>
            <p>If you have a 12+ month horizon, an emergency fund, risk capital you can afford to lose, and a DCA strategy — the data says buying at -49.6% from ATH has been profitable in every previous cycle.</p>
            <p>If you're looking for a quick flip, don't have emergency savings, or would panic at another 20% drop — this dip isn't for you. And that's okay. The most important rule in investing is <strong>don't invest in ways that jeopardize your peace of mind.</strong></p>

